cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

This paper is likely to belong to the sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the generalization performance of deep networks. It could also belong to cs.CV (Computer Vision) as deep networks are commonly used in image recognition tasks. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as deep learning is a subfield of AI. cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another possible sub-category as the paper deals with neural networks. Finally, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is a less likely sub-category as the paper does not explicitly deal with natural language processing, but it could be relevant if the networks were used for language-related tasks.
